                    "company": "Implementation Of The Global Fund\u2019s Programmatic Quality Assurance And Improvement Approach",
                    "description": "A focus on quality is critical to maintain the impact of unprecedented gains made by country programs have over the past 10 years in the fight against HIV/AIDS, tuberculosis and malaria. Within this scale up or increased coverage of life saving services, The Global Fund is working on the next steps necessary to strengthen health systems through the measurement of program and data quality, as well as utilization of the data. \n\nA critical update in 2016 will be to leverage country owned quality assurance and program improvement systems. This involves integrating an improved quality approach into a cycle of collecting and using data and other program information continuously. The mechanisms for rolling out this new approach to Programmatic Quality Assurance And Improvement by the Global Fund are currently in the planning stages.",
